The paper deals with the simplex algorithm for linear programming, which is a fundamental topic in computer science and optimization. The paper also introduces a geometric property of the constraint matrix, which suggests that it may belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) or discrete mathematics (cs.DS) sub-categories. The use of randomization and analysis of running time suggests that it may also belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) or theoretical computer science (cs.CC) sub-categories. Finally, the use of ideas from previous works suggests that it may also belong to the history and overview (cs.OH) sub-category.
